description: Pattern for creating CRUD modules in internal/module/ (based on organization)
globs: internal/module/**/*.go,internal/model/**/*.go
alwaysApply: false
---

# CRUD Module (organization pattern)

Reference: `internal/module/organization/`. Each module exposes a REST resource via Fiber + Uber FX.

## File structure

```
internal/module/{name}/
  module.go      # FX registration + routes
  handler.go     # HTTP (Fiber)
  service.go     # business rules
  repository.go  # data access (generic embed)
  dto.go         # input structs
  error.go       # domain errors (errors.New)
internal/model/{name}.go  # GORM entity
```

Register the module in `internal/app/module.go` with `{name}.Module`.

## module.go

```go
var Module = fx.Module("{name}",
    fx.Provide(NewRepository, NewService, NewHandler),
    fx.Invoke(func(api fiber.Router, handler *Handler) {
        handler.RegisterRoutes(api)
    }),
)
```

## repository.go

Embed the generic repository — do not reimplement CRUD:

```go
type Repository struct {
    *database.Repository[model.{Entity}]
}

func NewRepository(db *gorm.DB) *Repository {
    return &Repository{
        Repository: database.NewRepository[model.{Entity}](db),
    }
}
```

Add custom methods here only when the generic repository is not enough.

## service.go

- Accept `*Repository` in the constructor.
- Standard methods: `Create`, `Update`, `FindByID`, `FindBy`, `Delete`.
- Business validation in `Create`/`Update` (e.g. uniqueness via `filter.New` + `filter.WhereEq`).
- HTTP errors with `api.NewError(statusCode, ErrDomain)`; domain errors live in `error.go`.

## handler.go

- Struct with `service *Service` and `logger *logger.Logger`.
- `RegisterRoutes`: plural kebab-case group (`/organizations`).
- CRUD routes: `GET /:id`, `GET /`, `POST /`, `PUT /:id`, `DELETE /:id`.
- Log with `h.logger.Verbosef("%s %s {Action}", c.Method(), c.Path())`.
- `FindBy`: `filter.FromFiber[model.{Entity}](c)`.
- Bind body: `c.Bind().Body(dto)`; propagate `err` (global error handler handles it).
- `FindByID`/`FindBy`: respond with `c.Status(fiber.StatusOK).JSON(...)`.

## dto.go

```go
type Create{Entity}DTO struct {
    Name string `json:"name"`
}
type Update{Entity}DTO struct {
    Name string `json:"name"`
}
```

API-exposed fields use `json` tags in camelCase.

## error.go

```go
var Err{Entity}{Reason} = errors.New("{entity} {reason}")
```

## Model (internal/model)

```go
type {Entity} struct {
    ID        uuid.UUID `gorm:"type:uuid;primaryKey;default:gen_random_uuid()" json:"id"`
    CreatedAt time.Time `gorm:"type:timestamp;not null;default:CURRENT_TIMESTAMP;autoCreateTime" json:"createdAt"`
    UpdatedAt time.Time `gorm:"type:timestamp;not null;default:CURRENT_TIMESTAMP;autoUpdateTime" json:"updatedAt"`
}
```

Unique indexes: `uniqueIndex:{table}_{column}_key`. Create the corresponding SQL migration.

## Module creation checklist

1. Model in `internal/model/{name}.go`
2. Up/down migration in `migrations/`
3. Six files in `internal/module/{name}/`
4. Import in `internal/app/module.go`
5. Document DTOs and rules in `plan/modules/{name}.md` (if a plan exists)
